title: The Beatles - Kum Back (first ever Beatles bootleg, remastered)
description:
This is the remastered version of 'Kum Back', first widely spreaded bootleg of The Beatles, that was recorded from an unauthorised broadcast of the leaked demo acetate of 'Get Back' album in september 1969. 

Original LP version of this album wad released in December 1969 or in January 1970 by unknown label and later re-released by other pirates. It's release predates official release of 'Let It Be' album for a half of the year. Sound quality of the original LP was poor - that's why now it's near to imposible to found it's digital copy on the internet. This is the reason why this remastered version was made. It's sourse, just like a sourse for the origonal vinyl release, was a reel-to-reel recording of the WBCN FM broadcast of the 'Get Back' acetate. 

Tracklist:

1. Get Back
2. Can He Walk
3. Let It Be
4. Teddy Boy
5. Two Of Us

6. Don't Let Me Down
7. I've Got A Feeling
8. Long And Winding Road
9. For You Blue
10. I Dig A Pony
11. Get Back (reprise)

New covers for the CD-version are included. Flac, img +cue +EAC log. 

Greetings from Russia! Enjoy!
